00:00:06.220 --> 00:00:10.310
&gt;&gt; Kelly link was born in
Miami, Florida, where she lived

00:00:10.310 --> 00:00:13.380
in a quote half-finished
development for seven years;

00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:16.180
a place where her father
chased peacocks off the roof

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:18.320
of his car in the morning.

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:21.620
The rest of her childhood was
spent moving around from Tennessee

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:24.630
to Pennsylvania to North Carolina.

00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:27.030
This is so good because
I speak slower.

00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:29.010
I really wish you were
with me all the time.

00:00:29.010 --> 00:00:30.310
[ Laughter ]

00:00:30.310 --> 00:00:33.130
As a teenager, she spent
a lot of time in malls

00:00:33.130 --> 00:00:36.890
and owned a pet boa
constrictor named Baby.

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:38.460
Her parents loved books.

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:41.080
They could always be talked into
reading just one more chapter

00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:44.490
of the Narnia books, one
more chapter of the Hobbit.

00:00:44.490 --> 00:00:47.470
"I became deeply attached to an
edition of the Wonderful Wizard

00:00:47.470 --> 00:00:49.690
of Oz that belonged to
the dentist's office,"

00:00:49.690 --> 00:00:52.620
she told the New York Times,
"It wasn't in great shape,

00:00:52.620 --> 00:00:57.880
by which I mean someone had bled
on it, maybe multiple someone's.

00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:01.360
She wasn't happy about it, but my
mother finally bought it for me

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:03.930
so we could bring it home.

00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:07.270 position:56%
Shortly after graduating college,
Kelly won a sweepstakes while living

00:01:07.270 --> 00:01:10.000
in Scotland and got free
travel around the world.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:11.300
This is true.

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:14.100
She had to answer three
basic geographic questions

00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:16.040
and then a forth question
to break a tie

00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:19.090
which was why do you want
to go around the world?

00:01:19.090 --> 00:01:22.070
And she wrote because
you can't go through it.

00:01:22.070 --> 00:01:24.120
[ Laughter ]

00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:26.700
Kelly met her Husband, Gavin Grant,

00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:28.480
working at a used book
store in Boston.

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:32.940
And in 2000 they founded Small
Beer Press, a leading publisher

00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:37.010
of literary fantasy an science
fiction including her first two

00:01:37.010 --> 00:01:41.870
critically acclaimed collections of
stories Stranger than Fiction 2001

00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:45.370
and Magic for Beginners 2005.

00:01:45.370 --> 00:01:49.220
Kelly's many writing accolades
include three Hugo Awards,

00:01:49.220 --> 00:01:55.590 position:56%
a Nebula Award, Locus Award, a World
Fantasy Award, and a NEA fellowship

00:01:55.590 --> 00:01:59.690
in creative writing, which is a
highly competitive fellowship based

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:02.450
solely on artistic
excellence and selected

00:02:02.450 --> 00:02:05.040 position:56%
through an anonymous review process.

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:08.860
And any questions about the program
you can ask us right over there

00:02:08.860 --> 00:02:12.280
